# =============================================================================
# File: /opt/ansible-k3s-cluster/README.cluster-safety-rails
# =============================================================================
# Purpose:
#   Define the safety rails that prevent catastrophic or irreversible actions
#   within the cluster automation framework.
#
# Safety Rails:
#
#   1. Immutable Artifacts
#      - Nodes never modify kernel artifacts
#
#   2. Rollback-First Philosophy
#      - Every deployment must be reversible
#
#   3. No Cross-Role Contamination
#      - Builder never modifies node state
#      - Nodes never modify build state
#
#   4. Verification Required
#      - No deployment without passing verification pipeline
#
#   5. Integrity Enforcement
#      - wc-based manifest
#      - Drift detection
#
# Notes:
#   - These rails ensure long-term safety and operational resilience.
# =============================================================================
